criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

  -  Primary tracheal malignancies (the diseased tracheal extension is beyond standard
     resectability);

  -  Tracheoesophageal fistula (the diseased trachea-esophageal defect is beyond standard
     resectability);

  -  Tracheal stenosis (the diseased tracheal extension is beyond standard resectability);

  -  Tracheobronchial malacia(primitive or secondary),(the diseased tracheal extension is
     beyond standard resectability or medical treatment - endoluminal stenting or
     dilations)

Exclusion Criteria:

  -  Presence of systemic metastatic lesions and positive mediastinal lymph nodes
     (malignancies);

  -  Routine functional and psychological contraindication
